  "text": "The orally available medicines use is generally associated with the adverse effects together with hematological, cutaneous and gastrointestinal reactions, interrupttion in kidney and liver functioning and hypoglycemic coma [CITATION_1] . Therefore, it is crucial to continue the quest for newer and effective drugs. drum sativum [CITATION_2] , Croton cajucara [CITATION_3] , Eclipta alba [CITATION_4] , Embellica officinalis (D'souza et al., 2014) , Eruca sativa [CITATION_5] , Gaultheria trichophylla [CITATION_6] , Musa sapientum [CITATION_7] and Teramus labialus [CITATION_8] have shown antidiabetic activity.",
